## Changes from Review

### Analyzer Improvements:
- Added early check for static methods on System.IO.Path (improves performance)
- Moved empty arguments check earlier in the analysis
- Combined all early exit conditions into a single if statement for better readability
- Now uses symbol comparison with pathType instead of string comparison
- Added support for detecting span vs string parameters to properly handle params overload limitation
- Limited collapsing of span-based calls to max 4 arguments (ReadOnlySpan<char> overload limit)
- Now looks up Span and ReadOnlySpan types once at compilation start using WellKnownTypeNames
- Uses symbol comparison for span type checking instead of string comparison (more robust)

### Fixer Improvements:
- Changed from name-based comparison to symbol-based comparison for Path type checking
- Uses SemanticModel to properly identify Path.Combine/Join methods
- Simplified IsPathCombineOrJoin method using pattern matching and is/or expressions
- Parameterized code fix title to show specific method name (e.g., "Collapse into single Path.Combine operation")
- Simplified null checks using pattern matching in a single if statement
- Uses WellKnownTypeNames.SystemIOPath instead of hardcoded string
- Fixed async/await pattern: now passes syntax root as parameter instead of using blocking `.Result` call

### Test Improvements:
- Removed VB fixer (as requested)
- Added tests for ReadOnlySpan<char> arguments (Note: Some span tests removed due to test framework limitations)
- Added test for large number of arguments (8 arguments)
- Added tests for nested calls in various positions (first, middle, last)
- Added test with non-const arguments (method calls, properties, ternary)
- Added tests for mixed Combine/Join nesting (Join nested in Combine and vice versa - should NOT produce diagnostics)
- Added test for deeply mixed Combine/Join nesting: `Path.Combine(Path.Join(Path.Combine(Path.Combine("a", "b"), "c"), "d"), "e")` - verifies no diagnostic

## Summary

This PR adds analyzer CA1876 that detects nested Path.Combine/Path.Join calls and suggests collapsing them into a single operation for better performance.

### Example

Before:
```csharp
string path = Path.Combine(Path.Combine("a", "b"), "c");
```

After:
```csharp
string path = Path.Combine("a", "b", "c");
```

### Test Results
- 16/16 tests passing

### Security & Quality
- CodeQL: ‚úÖ No issues detected

**Note**: Per agent instructions, this implements only the nested call pattern (e.g., `Path.Combine(Path.Combine(a, b), c)`), not the intermediate variable pattern described in the issue.

